- "Beacons of knowledge" refers to institutions with high citation counts;
- "Financial nourishment" symbolizes the funding received by these institutions;
- "Shining brightly" metaphorically represents the top performers in academic and financial metrics;
- "Contributed in terms of citations" refers to the total citation counts;
- "Funding received" refers to the total funding amounts.

- "Illuminated the minds of many" metaphorically refers to high citation counts, indicating influential publications;
- "Patrons" refer to the funding agencies;
- "Treasures" symbolize the funding amounts provided to support the research;
- "Should remain unaided" refers to publications without any funding information, where the funding details would be null.

- "fruitful minds" refers to institutions that are highly productive in generating knowledge;
- "scholarly fruits" represents the publications created by these institutions;
- "most fertile" relates to institutions with the highest number of publications.
